<div class="about-wrap">

  <div class="bio-section">
    <div class="eyebrow">About</div>
    <h1 class="about-headline">I build systems where<br><em>software meets physics.</em></h1>
    <p class="about-p">I'm an Electrical &amp; Computer Engineering student at <strong>Vanderbilt University</strong> concentrating in Embedded Computing and Cyber-Physical Systems. My work lives at the boundary between hardware and software — register-level firmware, real-time control loops, industrial communication protocols, and full sensor-to-software data acquisition pipelines deployed on live research and production hardware.</p>
    <p class="about-p">I'm drawn to roles where engineering precision is not optional — medical devices, industrial automation, robotics, and autonomous platforms. Systems where a bug isn't a ticket, it's a consequence.</p>
  </div>

